\[
\text{Number of tablets needed} = \frac{\text{Total number of tablets}}{\text{Number of days}} = \frac{9 \text{ tablets}}{15 \text{ days}} = 0.6 \text{ tablets per day}
\]

Since the prescription is for 9 tablets, and she needs to take 15 days' worth, we can also directly calculate the total number of tablets needed:

\[
\text{Total number of tablets needed} = 9 \text{ tablets} \times \frac{15 \text{ days}}{9 \text{ tablets}} = 15 \text{ tablets}
\]

Therefore, Sandra needs to take 3 tablets per day for 15 days, which totals to 15 tablets. So, the number of tablets Sandra needs to take is:

\boxed{15}

